\f0\fs24 \cf3 <!$Scr_Ps::0><$Scr_Ps::1>
\f2\fs32 Before use, the equipment under test must be secured, locked out, and grounded to discharge any residual capacitive static charge. The meter is connected between an insulated conductor and ground, and then the test voltage is applied for 60 seconds or until the resistance  reading stops changing, whichever comes first. The meter measures the current flow through the insulation, and using ohm\'92s law, calculates and displays the insulation resistance. 
